I modified the recipe a bit. I used shallots, not onions, more garlic, more balsamic, more mustard, added about 1/3 cup of white wine (near the end), a splash of chicken broth, portabello mushrooms, a tbsp of butter, and shredded parmesan at the end with the basil. I tasted it right after and was a bit disappointed after all the modifications I made. However, once it sat a bit (I made it late at night for the next day) I think it tasted better. It needs more umph. more flavor. the sauce needs to be reduced. I think the sauce tastes great, but I really wish it was thicker. I guess it could be thickened up pretty easily with some cornstarch or something. Thanks to all the previous reviewers - I think your input made the outcome better!! I agree that adding cream to the sauce would be awesome.

