Rating: 3
I also would double the sauce, and, at the end add some real butter or cream to round out the sauce. I also agree with adding mushrooms to the sauce.This rule of thumb of 2 tbs of balsamic Vinegar and one teas of creole or whole grain mustard works well in other recipes. If you make a roast , on the side saute some onions and garlic, and then a bunch of chopped mushrooms with the pan drippings and low salt broth added to cover the mushrooms about half way. After the mushrooms are softened add the balsamic vinegar/mustard combination mentioned above one at a time until the sauce is sufficiently thick. Then add two or three ounces of real butter of cream, bring to a slight boil for just a second or two, stir and use as sauce over the roast.

